## Migration to ROS2
The core interfaces live in [src/core/](src/core/) and are intentionally ROS-agnostic. A later ROS2 Jazzy migration should add a bridge layer instead of rewriting the control unit.

## Current limitation
The real driver in [src/drivers/piper_driver.py](src/drivers/piper_driver.py) already targets the official `C_PiperInterface_V2` API, but gripper travel defaults to a normalized-to-millimeter mapping that may need calibration on your hardware. Mock mode is fully runnable now.
